# wingsys (Windows Game System)
Create console games on windows
> [!IMPORTANT]  
> This version of gsys (Game System) is meant for windows users only.  
> [[See the list of versions](#other-versions)]

## Issues
You can report issues in [the gsys GitHub repository](https://www.github.com/mgismissing/gs/issues).

## Installation
```
pip install wingsys
```

## Contents
### 1. `Screen`
```python
(function) def __init__(
    self,
    forecolor: str = "WHITE",
    backcolor: str = "BLACK",
    width: int = 32,
    height: int = 16,
    border: list = ["-", "|", "#", "#", "#", "#"],
    stdchar: str = " "
    )
```
`forecolor: str = "WHITE"` defines the color of text that will be displayed on the screen.  
`backcolor: str = "BLACK"` defines the background color of the screen.  
`width: int = 32` defines the width (in characters) of the screen.  
`height: int = 16` defines the height (in characters) of the screen.  
`border: list = ["-", "|", "#", "#", "#", "#"]` defines the border of the screen. [see [Custom Borders](#custom-borders)]  
`stdchar: str = " "` defines the character that the screen will be filled with.

*\*Work In Progress, the documentation will be complete with version 0.2\**

## Custom Borders
The [`Screen`](#1-screen) Borders can be customized. The border follows this scheme to be drawn around the screen:  
`["1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6"]`  
Will become  
```
3111111114
2########2
2########2
2########2
2########2
5111111116
```
("`#`" is the screen).

